net.objectof.model.query

Interface QueryResolver

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FallbackResolver

    public interface QueryResolver
    Defines how to resolve simple key o value relationships using a specific Package implementation. More complex queries are resolved using set operations on the results of these simple key o value queries
    Author:
    NAS

      java.util.Set<java.lang.String> resolve(int aLimit, java.lang.String key, Relation relation, java.lang.Object value)
      Examines keyed elements within a Package to find ones which satisfy a Relation with the given value.

    • Method Detail

      • resolve

        java.util.Set<java.lang.String> resolve(int aLimit,
                                        java.lang.String key,
                                        Relation relation,
                                        java.lang.Object value)
                                 throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException,
                                        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Examines keyed elements within a Package to find ones which satisfy a Relation with the given value. Kind is implicit in this resolution, as it should remain constant through a higher level of resolution.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to match against
        relation - the Relation the given value should satisfy with the values being examined
        value - the value to compare the examined values against
        Returns:
        a List of Strings representing the Label of the matched elements
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
